trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.

Translates the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Point3D"></xref> structure by the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure and returns the result as a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Point3D"></xref> structure.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure used to translate the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Point3D"></xref> structure.
Adds two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structures and returns the result as a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.

Retrieves the angle required to rotate the first specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure into the second specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
Signed angles do not extend into [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_3d](~/includes/tlasharptla-3d-md.md)] space, so an angle between 0 and 180 degrees is returned.
The angle in degrees needed to rotate vector1 into vector2.
Calculates the cross product of two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structures.

Divides the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure by the specified scalar and returns the result as a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref>.
Calculates the dot product of two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structures.

Two <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> structures are equal if the values of their <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.X%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.Y%2A>, and <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.Z%2A> properties are the same.
Because the value of a <xref:System.Double> can lose precision when operated upon, a comparison between two <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> values that are logically equal might fail.
`true` if the , , and components of vector1 and vector2 are equal; `false` otherwise.
Because the value of a <xref:System.Double> can lose precision when operated upon, a comparison between two <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> values that are logically equal might fail.
The instance of Vector to compare against this instance.

Determines whether the specified object is a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure and whether the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.Y"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.Z"></xref> properties of the specified <xref href="System.Object"></xref> are equal to the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.X"></xref>, <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.Y"></xref>, and <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D.Z"></xref> properties of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
If `o` is not a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> structure, this method returns `false`.
Because the value of a <xref:System.Double> can lose precision when operated upon, a comparison between two <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> values that are logically equal might fail.
`true` if o is a structure and is identical with this structure; `false` otherwise.
Gets a hash code for this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
A hash code for this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
Gets the length of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
The length of a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> is sometimes referred to as the magnitude.
Gets the square of the length of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
The length of a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> is sometimes referred to as the magnitude.
The square of the length of this <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.

Multiplies the specified scalar by the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure and returns the result as a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref>.

Multiplies the specified <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure by the specified scalar and returns the result as a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref>.

The transformation to apply to the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
Returns the result of transforming vector by matrix3D.
The vector has the same magnitude as before, but its direction is now opposite.
A normalized <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> maintains its direction but its magnitude becomes `1`.
The resulting <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> is often called a unit vector.
A <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> is normalized by dividing the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D> by its magnitude.
Adds two <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structures and returns the result as a <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Media3D.Vector3D"></xref> structure.
